details.floor: Hewn Stone (DC 10 to charge or run)
details.history: The dungeon was created by dwarves as a tomb. It was eventually conquered by invaders, and has been conquered and altered many times since then.
details.illumination: Average (shadowy in corridors, lamps or torches in most rooms)

detail.room_features: Someone has scrawled "The Sapphire Order looted this place" on the north wall, and a warped holy symbol lies in the north-west corner of the room
Spirals of red stones cover the floor, and a forge and anvil sit in the south side of the room

monster: Treasure: 1400 cp, 400 sp, 40 gp, 2 x diamond (50 gp), bloodstone (50 gp), 3 x citrine (50 gp), 2 x moonstone (50 gp), 2 x star rose quartz (50 gp)
detail.room_features: A magical mirror on the west wall answers questions with insults, and spirals of blue stones cover the floor
A balcony hangs from the south wall, and a large kiln and coal bin sit in the north-west corner of the room
A large kiln and coal bin sit in the north-west corner of the room, and a dagger hilt lies in the north-west corner of the room

monster: Hobgoblin (cr 1/2, mm 186) and 2 x Goblin (cr 1/4, mm 166); deadly, 200 xp
Treasure: 2200 cp, 700 sp, 90 gp, blue quartz (10 gp), 2 x eye agate (10 gp), obsidian (10 gp), tiger eye (10 gp), turquoise (10 gp)
detail.room_features: The floor is covered with slime, and several pieces of rotten bread are scattered throughout the room

A magical shrine in the south-west corner of the room grants the ability to detect magic (for one day) to whomever offers a prayer, and someone has scrawled "You cannot kill it with magic" on the west wall
An enchanted pool in the north-east corner of the room ages whomever drinks from it (but only once), and a rusted breastplate lies in the south side of the room

monster: Orc (cr 1/2, mm 246) and 1 x Half-ogre (cr 1, mm 238); deadly, 300 xp

Treasure: 2300 cp, 1700 sp, 60 gp, banded agate (10 gp), 2 x eye agate (10 gp), hematite (10 gp), lapis lazuli (10 gp), malachite (10 gp), 2 x moss agate (10 gp), obsidian (10 gp), tiger eye (10 gp), 2 x turquoise (10 gp)

detail.room_features: A narrow ledge runs along the south and west walls, and a tile labyrinth covers the floor

monster: Hobgoblin (cr 1/2, mm 186) and 2 x Goblin (cr 1/4, mm 166); deadly, 200 xp

detail.room_features: A stone sarcophagus sits in the center of the room, and the floor is covered with mould
A faded and torn tapestry hangs from the west wall, and a pile of trash lies in the south-east corner of the room

wandering_monsters.4: Ogre Zombie (cr 2, mm 316); deadly, 450 xp, investigating a strange noise
wandering_monsters.5: Goblin Boss (cr 1, mm 166) and 1 x Goblin (cr 1/4, mm 166); medium, 250 xp, hunting for food
